<DOCNO> AP880702-0002 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
postal workers cheered as the city 
council approved a law requiring vicious animals to wear 
fluorescent yellow collars and some owners to take out liability 
insurance on their pets 
the law passed thursday in response to pit bull attacks 
requires vicious animals to wear the collars which signify the 
wearer has attacked humans or other animals or has been legally 
declared likely to do so without provocation 
the ordinance also requires that an animal declared vicious be 
tattooed with the number that appears on the permit allowing the 
owner to keep it inside the city limits 
in addition owners of vicious animals can be forced to carry at 
least 100000 in liability insurance to keep the pets in the city 
and can be fined up to 2000 for violations of the new ordinance 
local letter carriers who gathered in council chambers cheered 
thursday when the ordinance was passed 
a galveston postal worker was severely bitten by a pit bull in 
january and an 83yearold man died from wounds inflicted in a 
november attack by two pit bulls 
i hope this action today will save lives in the future 
mayor jan coggeshall said 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

