symphony orchestra observed the 50th birthday of its music shed 
with a 50candle cake and a reunion of musicians and ushers from 
the sheds first concert 
also in honor of the halfcenturyold concert hall symphony 
trustees voted friday to rename the music shed after the late 
conductor serge koussevitzky founder of the prestigious summer 
music festival who inaugurated the hall with a performance of 
beethovens ninth symphony and bachs cantata no 80 in 1938 
george h kidder symphony president played tapes of 
koussevitzky giving his reasons for choosing beethovens ninth 
symphony for the inaugural performance which the symphony 
orchestra played again friday night 
on this significant day in the musical life i have selected 
to give the ninth symphony not only because it is the greatest 
masterpiece in the musical literature but also to hear the voices 
of tanglewood repeating german poet johann shillers great words 
calling all nations to brotherhood koussevitsky said on one of 
the tapes 
during a break in the program kidder also introduced several 
people who had been at the 1938 performance including three ushers 
orchestra members and concertgoers who were present at the aug 
4 1938 inaugural performance were honored at a luncheon friday at 
koussevitzkys home seranak 
