<TEXT>
yegor k ligachev the no 2 man in the kremlin 
provided an unprecedented look into the inner workings of the 
soviet leadership with his description of the events that brought 
mikhail s gorbachev to power 
ligachev said friday at the communist party conference that 
gorbachev had crucial support from himself andrei a gromyko and 
kgb chief viktor g chebrikov when he became party general 
secretary in march 1985 gromyko now president was foreign 
minister at the time 
ligachev recounting emotions and experiences in a manner rare 
for a member of the traditionally stoic party politburo disputed 
claims from ousted moscow communist party boss boris n yeltsin 
that he had slowed reform 
he said he had been deeply worried about the fate of the country 
during the final days of leonid i brezhnev who ruled from 1964 to 
1982 in a time of stagnation 
more very disquieting days and hours came when the party 
elite assembled to choose a successor to konstantin u chernenko in 
march 1985 ligachev said 
fate put me in the center of action he said we could 
have made quite different decisions and sometimes i think what 
would have happened to the country after that he told the 
conference delegates 
with the support of chebrikov gromyko politburo member mikhail 
s solomentsev and some regional party leaders the only correct 
decision was taken he added 
gromyko made the nominating speech proposing gorbachev as 
general secretary after chernenkos death but ligachevs account 
was the first to suggest solomentsev had supported gorbachev 
his comments appeared to confirm rumors that circulated at the 
time that former moscow party boss viktor v grishin an ally of 
chernenko and brezhnev had made a lastminute attempt to secure 
the leadership 
ligachevs statements which were televised also could boost 
gromyko and solomentsev a day after they were criticized by name at 
the fourday conference which ended friday 
gromyko 78 was foreign minister for 28 years before accepting 
the largely ceremonial presidency in july 1985 he and solomentsev 
have sat on the policysetting central committee since the early 
1960s 
the country came to a crisis before gorbachev became leader 
ligachev said he spoke of corruption lack of discipline and 
alcoholism 
because of a lack of frankness even the party was in 
danger he said 
all revolutionary parties that died did so because they were 
afraid to talk about their weaknesses he said 
ligachev spoke of his career during the brezhnev years 
in the years of stagnation i worked and lived in siberia 
said ligachev the communist party leader in the siberian city of 
tomsk from 196583 i say with pride that i built socialism and 
there were millions of such people 
referring with a touch of humor to the russian practice of 
sending misfits and disidents to siberia ligachev said perhaps 
we worked like that because we knew that they wouldnt send us 
farther than siberia 
