thinking 
poland and hungary have gone the farthest in matching or even 
exceeding soviet leader mikhail s gorbachevs reforms in the 
economy and politics 
gorbachev who closed the fourday conference friday will be 
paying a sixday visit to warsaw beginning july 11 
the new thinking at the conference creates fresh 
possibilities of a gradual demilitarization and humanization of 
international relations polish foreign ministry spokesman stefan 
staniszewski told a news conference thursday 
in czechoslovakia where officials privately say they are 
waiting to see whether gorbachev will strengthen his position at 
the conference the communist party daily rude pravo said the event 
will be an inspiration and a source of practical enlightment for 
us 
if the kremlin leader gets a mandate for more radical reforms 
it would increase pressure on czechoslovakias leaders installed 
after moscow crushed gorbachevlike reforms with tanks 20 years ago 
to adopt political change and to reform economic structure more 
quickly 
the ideas are worth thinking about rude pravo said 
in yugoslavia which broke with moscow over ideological issues 
40 years ago the state press carried lengthy reports from the 
conference describing it as historic dramatic and exceptionally 
open 
yugoslav media pointed to gorbachevs words that there will be 
no prosperity for socialism without fundamental and deep 
democratization of the soviet society 
all the communist leaderships in eastern europe many of them 
now more secretive and orthodox than the modern kremlin have 
