we can speak our minds openly and directly without being 
afraid of anything said ivan i maximov a balding metalworker 
from the siberian town of biisk 
during a friday afternoon break in the final session of the 
first party conference in 47 years soviet television broadcast the 
live interviews in the lobby of the kremlins palace of congresses 
with some of the 5000 delegates 
most of the discussion during the broadcast focused on what one 
delegate called the highlight of fridays session of the fourday 
conference the speech by yeltsin a former gorbachev protege 
its the most heated discussion we have heard in a long 
time a grayhaired delegate told the television correspondent 
a studio anchorman began the 30minute broadcast and then 
switched live to the correspondent on the scene 
delegates had just ended floor debate about yeltsins speech in 
which he asked to be cleared of blame for criticizing other soviet 
