the discussion spilled over into the television interviews some 
delegates told viewers they supported yeltsin while others 
condemned his remarks as politically incorrect 
yeltsin was fired as moscow party boss and removed from his post 
as a nonvoting member of the ruling politburo after a bitter 
speech to the partys central committee last october in which he 
complained that economic reforms had stalled and asked to be 
relieved of his duties his speech at that meeting has never been 
published 
maximov the delegate from biisk said it is difficult for 
people to make up their minds about whether yeltsins criticism was 
justified because his central committee speech remains secret 
glasnost must be deep then such questions wouldnt arise he 
told the television interviewer 
during the conference soviet television and radio provided 
