new appraisals of a proposed prison site for which 
gov michael dukakis administration has asked 10 million to buy 
from developers put the value of the land at under 6 million 
according to sources 
the state wants to build a 500bed prison on the hilltop land in 
new braintree developers who one critic of the project alleges 
are friends of the democratic presidential candidate sought 95 
million for the land two years ago 
the fbi is conducting a preliminary inquiry into allegations 
that the dukakis administration leaked word to the developers of 
state interest in the land they bought it from a church for 3 
million 
dukakis who the fbi says is not under investigation himself 
and the developers deny the allegation or any association with each 
other 
dukakis asked about the controversy in recent weeks has 
reiterated his position that the state will not pay one dime 
more than the fair market value of the property 
three sources all speaking on the condition of anonymity told 
