<TEXT>
here is the text of sen robert byrds 
response to president reagans weekly radio address broadcast 
saturday 
good afternoon this is senator robert byrd of west virginia 
this monday is the fourth of july for most americans the 
fourth of july is a day to spend with family and friends we hold 
picnics go to the beach march in parades and look forward to 
fireworks at night we celebrate our freedom it is a good day to 
be an american we share our love of country around the barbecue 
pit and the picnic table 
we take stock of nations prosperity between innings during the 
annual softball game we see the future in the delight of our 
children as they watch the fireworks light up the sky it is a day 
of quite patriotism reaffirmation and thankfulness 
we thank god for our good fortune that we are americans we 
reaffirm our commitment to the legacy given to us by our 
forbearers we pray for those americans upon whom misfortune has 
fallen 
but this fourth is a little different it is different because 
this year we must choose a new path for america this is an 
election year were about to choose a new president 
and on this fourth of july it is a time for reflection as well 
as celebration it is a time to remember what has made america 
great and to use those traditional strengths as we contemplate the 
future our nation has unfinished business 
our foreign competition is still beating us at our own game 
our children are not getting the education they deserve the 
american dream of owning a home seems to be almost out of reach for 
the next generation drug dealers flood the market with dope and 
death the american family the bedrock of our nations foundation 
is changing and needs new policies to preserve it 
what is most disturbing is the erosion of the public trust 
wall street has been rocked by scandal our national security is 
being endangered by greed honesty and integrity seem to be in 
short supply for some americans those may seem to be reasons 
enough to turn away from politics from making a choice about the 
future nothing is ever going to change they say throwing up 
their hands in despair why vote at all 
but if this had been the attitude of thomas jefferson and the 
other great founders of our nation on the first fourth of july 
where would we be today let us reject the cynicism that says that 
things cannot be improved 
you the people have the power to change things and to let 
those in high places know what you expect america has unfinished 
business 
america was not founded on cynicism it was founded on hope by 
strong people who built a new country by making new choices however 
difficult america was built on love of country belief in the 
common man hard and honest work optimism and religious faith it 
is your government and it can reflect your values and it can help 
to solve americas problem but you have to participate 
america can deal with its drug problem american can educate our 
children better american can adapt to the changing needs of the 
family america can meet our security commitments without busting 
the national budget america can meet our energy needs america can 
protect the environment and america can demand a fair deal from 
our trading partners overseas americans want a restoration of 
integrity and common decency those are values that we all share 
and understand 
i come from west virginia the state where patriotism and family 
are cherished traditions i know most other americans are like that 
too i have great faith in this country when we americans put our 
minds to it we can solve our problems and americans are always 
willing to imagine something new and better for their country 
americans are optimists 
this fourth of july then let us remember our strengths our 
heritage and our power to determine our own fate we can give 
america a new beginning celebrate your freedom in the most 
meaningful way this year participate exercise that most 
important uniquely american privilege register and vote get 
involved 
</TEXT>
