<TEXT>
the communist party will review the qualifications 
of each of its 20 million members before the end of the year a 
move that could help strengthen mikhail s gorbachevs political 
base 
gorbachev directed that the examination of party members be 
conducted in the open and not through discussion behind the 
scenes the official communist party newspaper pravda said 
saturday 
the fourday communist party conference that ended friday 
approved a call for reevaluating party membership as well as 
backing gorbachevs program for a stronger legislature presidency 
and a 10year limit on the terms of party and government officials 
pravda said the conference considered it necessary to carry 
out this year a campaign in party organizations governed by 
the decisions of the conference about reform of the political 
system democratization of party life 
such a reevaluation of party membership could become a 
widespread effort to force opponents of gorbachevs reforms out of 
the party but it is more likely to be targeted against the idle 
and corrupt 
not a single honest man should be left outside perestroika 
gorbachev said in his speech opening the conference tuesday 
but the communist party chief also has said that the criterion 
for judging party members is their attitude toward his reform 
effort a limited housecleaning could be expected to strengthen 
gorbachev by eliminating some of the most intransigent opponents of 
reform and improving the partys effectiveness 
and it could improve the image of the party which the 
policymaking central committee criticized before the conference as 
having a bureaucratic stranglehold on the economy and government 
communists must go through a lengthy selection process and 
ideological training before being granted membership in the party 
a prerequisite for advancement to positions of responsibility in 
soviet society about one of 10 soviet adults is a member of the 
party 
although conference delegates backed the review of the 
membership roll it is unlikely they would have gone along with a 
widespread campaign against conservatives 
many of the speeches to the conference struck a tone 
considerably more conservative than gorbachevs and the official 
press said before the conference that midlevel party officials had 
rammed through slates of delegates despite gorbachevs call for an 
open democratic election procedure 
the resolution calling for the review of party membership also 
called for a a division of power between the party apparatus and 
local governing councils or soviets 
gorbachev proposed at the conference to get the party out of 
daytoday management of affairs and leave that to responsible 
government officials and plant managers 
the resolution was the only one of seven from the party 
conference published by the soviet press saturday and it was 
uncertain when the rest of the resolutions would be released 
the conference of 5000 communists from around the country 
called to review progress on gorbachevs reforms and chart a course 
for the future acted on the party review at the urging of the 
central committee and gorbachev 
gorbachev has told party bureaucrats they must either get behind 
him or get out of the way 
but he said the party still must give its members a chance 
many of these who only recently were regarded inactive and had 
lost contact with the party branch who had been regarded as dead 
wood are now trying to find their place in life gorbachev said 
the very certification process should be a school of educating 
communists gorbachev added 
</TEXT>
