nineteenyearold steffi graf defeated 
eighttime wimbledon winner martina navratilova on saturday to 
capture her first wimbledon crown and continue her domination of 
womens tennis this year 
the west germans 57 62 61 victory at the all england 
tennis championships stopped navratilova from winning a record nine 
singles titles on the famed grass courts 
grafs win follows victories at two earlier grand slam events 
this year the australian and french opens if she takes the us 
open in september she will become the first person in 18 years to 
sweep the grand slam circuit in the same year 
graf who took over the no 1 ranking in the world from 
navratilova last august became the youngest wimbledon womens 
champion since 17yearold american maureen connelly won in 1952 
she is the first german woman to win since cilly aussem in 1931 
american navratilova 31 did not lose without a fight winning 
six games in a row to wrap up the first set and taking a 20 lead 
in the second but then graf used her stinging forehand and 
devastating speed to take the final two sets 
west germanys boris becker and swedens stefan edberg meet 
sunday in the mens final 
