this act of disobedience which signifies the outright 
rejection of the roman primate constitutes a schismatic act 
the pope said noting that the prelates involved have incurred 
the grave penalty of excommunication as foreseen under 
ecclesiastical discipline 
he called lefebvres action contradictory to the church 
traditions lefebvre says he represents 
one cannot remain faithful to tradition by breaking ecclesial 
ties with the man whom christ himself in the person of the apostle 
peter entrusted the ministry of the unity of his church the 
letter said 
the pope said the schism should encourage theologians to make a 
renewed examination of the second vatican council reforms 
especially on those points of doctrine which perhaps because of 
their novelty have not yet been understood well by some sectors in 
the church 
all catholics he said should reflect sincerely on their own 
faithfulness to the tradition of the church 
lefebvre 82 was suspended from his priestly duties in 1976 by 
pope paul vi but in defiance of the vatican he has ordained 220 
priests who are officiating in 28 countries lefebvres movement 
also has an estimated 200 seminarians 
those excommunicated with lefebvre and castro mayer were the 
four new bishops bernard fellay bernard tissier de mallerais 
richard williamson and alfonso de galaretta 
an excommunicated roman catholic is unable to receive the church 
sacraments which include the eucharist and last rites 
the schism provoked by lefebvre was the first since 1870 when 
the old catholics broke with the vatican over the doctrine of papal 
infallibility 
